The Instructions of Shuruppak 𒂄𒊒𒁉𒀀𒂔𒂵

(ETCSL 5.6.1, composite text, ~280 lines; wisdom instructions of Šuruppag to his son Zi-ud-sura)

1.
𒌓 𒊑𒀀 𒌓 𒋤𒁺 𒊑𒀀
ud re-a ud su3-ra2 re-a
1-13. In those days, in those far remote days, in those nights, in those faraway nights, in those years, in those far remote years, at that time the wise one who knew how to speak in elaborate words lived in the Land; Šuruppag, the wise one, who knew how to speak with elaborate words lived in the Land. Šuruppag gave instructions to his son; Šuruppag, the son of Ubara-Tutu gave instructions to his son Zi-ud-sura: My son, let me give you instructions: you should pay attention! Zi-ud-sura, let me speak a word to you: you should pay attention! Do not neglect my instructions! Do not transgress the words I speak! The instructions of an old man are precious; you should comply with them!

2.
𒈪 𒊑𒀀 𒈪 𒁁𒁺 𒊑𒀀
ji6 re-a ji6 ba9-ra2 re-a

3.
𒈬 𒊑𒀀 𒈬 𒋤𒁺 𒊑𒀀
mu re-a mu su3-ra2 re-a

4.
𒌓𒁀 𒄑𒌆 𒌇 𒅗 𒃴 𒅗 𒍮𒀀 𒌦𒈠 𒋾𒆷𒀀
ud-ba jectug2 tuku inim galam inim zu-a kalam-ma til3-la-a

5.
? 𒄑𒌆 𒌇 𒅗 𒃴 𒅗 𒍮𒀀 𒌦𒈠 𒋾𒆷𒀀
curuppagki jectug2 tuku inim galam inim zu-a kalam-ma til3-la-a

6.
𒂊 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾 𒈾𒈬𒌦𒊑𒊑
curuppagki-e dumu-ni-ra na na-mu-un-ri-ri

7.
? 𒌉 𒂬𒌅𒌅𒁲
curuppagki dumu ubara-tu-tu-ke4

8.
𒍣𒌓𒋤𒁺 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾 𒈾𒈬𒌦𒊑𒊑
zi-ud-su3-ra2 dumu-ni-ra na na-mu-un-ri-ri

9.
𒌉𒈬 𒈾 𒂵𒊑 𒈾𒊑𒈬 𒃶𒆪
dumu-ju10 na ga-ri na-ri-ju10 he2-dab5

10.
𒍣𒌓𒋤𒁺 𒅗 𒂵𒊏𒀊𒅗 𒄑𒌆𒉿𒎓𒉣 𒃶𒅎𒅆𒀝
zi-ud-su3-ra2 inim ga-ra-ab-dug4 jizzal he2-em-ci-ak

11.
𒈾𒂵𒈬 𒋗 𒉆𒉈𒁇𒊑
na-rig5-ga-ju10 cu nam-bi2-bar-re

12.
𒅗 𒅗𒂵𒈬 𒈾𒀊𒋫𒁄𒂊𒉈
inim dug4-ga-ju10 na-ab-ta-bal-e-de3

13.
𒈾𒊑 𒀊𒁀 𒃻𒆗𒆷𒀀𒀭 𒄘𒍮 𒃶𒅎𒅆𒅅
na-ri ab-ba nij2-kal-la-am3 gu2-zu he2-em-ci-jal2

14.
𒀲𒀴𒃡 𒅗𒁲 𒈾𒀊𒉚𒉚 𒉠𒍮 𒊭𒊏𒀊𒅆𒀧
dur3ur3 gu3-di na-ab-sa10-sa10 murub4-zu ca-ra-ab-si-il
14. You should not buy a donkey which brays; it will split your midriff.

15.
𒃷 𒆜𒆷 𒉆𒉈𒌈𒂷𒂷 𒉆𒍂 𒄘 𒂷𒀀𒀭
gan2 kaskal-la nam-bi2-ib2-ja2-ja2 nam-silig gu2 ja2-am3
15-18. You should not locate a field on a road. You should not plough a field at a road or a path. You should not make a well in your field: people will cause damage on it for you. You should not place your house next to a public square: there is always a crowd there.

16.
𒀀𒊮 𒅗𒄊𒅗 𒉆𒁀𒂊𒀳𒊒 𒍣 𒁑𒂵𒀀𒀭
a-cag4 ka-jiri3-ka nam-ba-e-ur11-ru zi bulug-ga-am3

17.
𒃷𒍮𒀀𒀭 𒇥 𒈾𒀭𒉌𒆕𒂊𒂗 𒌦𒂊 𒊭𒊑𒅁𒅆𒌨𒅆𒌨
gan2-zu-am3 pu2 na-an-ni-du3-e-en uj3-e ca-ri-ib-hul-hul

18.
𒂍 𒋻 𒂼 𒉆𒉈𒅁𒇲𒂊 𒆟𒁕 𒅅𒆷𒀀𒀭
e2 sila dajal nam-bi2-ib-la2-e KEC2-da jal2-la-am3

19.
𒋗𒂃𒀀 𒉡𒂊𒉐 𒇽𒁉 𒊭𒁀𒂊𒆪𒁉
cu-du8-a nu-e-tum3 lu2-bi ca-ba-e-dab5-be2
19-20. You should not vouch for someone: that man will have a hold on you; and you yourself, you should not let somebody vouch for you.

20.
𒍝𒂊 𒋗𒂃𒀀 𒉆𒈬𒂊𒀝𒂊
za-e cu-du8-a nam-mu-e-ak-e

21.
𒇽𒊏 𒅆𒂃 𒈾𒀭𒀝𒂊 𒍍𒁉 𒊭𒊑𒅁𒋢𒋢
lu2-ra igi-du8 na-an-ak-e uru2-bi ca-ri-ib-su-su
21. You should not make an inspection on a man: the flood will give it back to you.

22.
𒆠 𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈𒁕𒅗 𒉆𒉈𒁺𒉈
ki du14-da-ka nam-bi2-du-de3
22-27. You should not loiter about where there is a quarrel; you should not let the quarrel make you a witness. You should not let yourself be involved in a quarrel. You should not cause a quarrel. Stand aside from a quarrel; you should not take another road.

23.
𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈𒉈 𒇽 𒆠𒅗𒈠 𒉆𒁀𒂊𒆭𒆭
du14-de3 lu2 ki-inim-ma nam-ba-e-ku4-ku4

24.
𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈𒉈 𒉎𒍮 𒉆𒁀
du14-de3 ni2-zu nam-ba

25.
𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈 𒉆𒀝𒉈𒂗
du14 nam-ak-de3-en

26.
𒆍 𒂍𒃲𒆷𒀀𒀭 𒁀𒊏𒋛𒂵
ka2 e2-gal-la-am3 ba-ra-sig9-ga

27.
𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈𒉈 𒁇𒁇𒋫 𒁺𒁺𒁀 𒅔𒉡𒍑 𒋻 𒉽𒊏 𒉆𒈠𒉌𒅁𒁺
du14-de3 bar-bar-ta gub-gub-ba in-nu-uc sila kur2-ra nam-ma-ni-ib-du

28.
𒃻 𒉆𒈬𒅗𒅗 𒉎𒍮 𒉆𒈬𒁁𒂊
nij2 nam-mu-zuh-zuh ni2-zu nam-mu-bad-e
28-31. You should not steal anything; you should not endanger yourself. You should not break into a house; you should not wish for the money chest. A thief is a lion, but after he has been caught, he will be a slave. My son, you should not commit robbery; you should not cut yourself with an axe.

29.
𒂍 𒈾𒀀𒀭𒉌𒌋𒂊𒂗 𒈪𒅆𒅖𒊏 𒀠 𒉆𒈨
e2 na-a-an-ni-bur3-e-en mi-si-ic-ra al nam-me

30.
𒉎𒍮 𒊊 𒈾𒉆 𒌌𒆪 𒊕 𒈾𒉆
ni2-zu pirij na-nam ul-dab5 saj na-nam

31.
𒌉𒈬 𒄤 𒉆𒈬𒅇𒀝𒂊 𒉎𒍮 𒂅𒀀𒀭 𒉆𒉈𒅁𒁇𒊑𒂊
dumu-ju10 sa-gaz nam-mu-u3-ak-e ni2-zu tun3-am3 nam-bi2-ib-bar-re-e

32.
𒀴 𒂅𒆦𒆦𒅆 𒈾𒀭𒀝 𒉎𒍮 𒈾𒀭
nitah nijir-si na-an-ak ni2-zu na-an
32-34. You should not make a young man best man. You should not play around with a married young woman: the slander could be serious. My son, you should not sit alone in a chamber with a married woman.

33.
𒆠𒂖 𒁮 𒌇𒁕 𒂊𒉈 𒉆𒈬𒌦𒉈𒂊 𒅗 𒋝𒂵 𒈤𒀀𒀭
ki-sikil dam tuku-da e-ne nam-mu-un-ne-e inim sig-ga mah-am3

34.
𒌉𒈬 𒆠𒍇𒈾 𒇽 𒁮 𒌇𒁕 𒂉 𒉆𒉈𒂊𒂷𒂷
dumu-ju10 daggan-na lu2 dam tuku-da dur2 nam-bi2-e-ja2-ja2

35.
𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈 𒉆𒊬𒊬𒉈 𒉎𒍮 𒈾𒀭𒄫𒂖𒇲
du14 nam-mu2-mu2-de3 ni2-zu na-an-pe-el-la2
35-38. You should not pick a quarrel; you should not disgrace yourself. You should not boast; then your words will be trusted. You should not deliberate for too long: you cannot bear ...... glances.

36.
𒈜 𒉆𒍀𒍀 𒊕 𒄘 𒊩𒊩𒆷
lul nam-gur5-gur5 saj gu2 sal-sal-la

37.
𒅗 𒉆𒋻𒋻𒊑𒂊𒂗 𒅗𒍮 𒃻𒊏𒀀𒀭
ka nam-tar-tar-re-e-en inim-zu jar-ra-am3

38.
𒀜 𒉆𒄄𒄄 𒅆 𒂂 𒉡𒈬𒌦𒁕𒅍
ad nam-gi4-gi4 igi dugud nu-mu-un-da-il2

39.
𒇽𒁕 𒃻 𒅗𒀀 𒉆𒈬𒁕𒅥𒂊
lu2-da ninda zuh-a nam-mu-da-gu7-e
39-41. You should not eat stolen food with a thief. You should not sink your hand into blood. After you have apportioned the bones, you will be made to restore the ox, you will be made to restore the sheep.

40.
𒋗𒍮 𒍗𒀀𒀭 𒈾𒁲𒉌𒅁𒋢𒋢
cu-zu uc2-am3 na-di-ni-ib-su-su

41.
𒄊 𒄯𒊑 𒄞 𒊭𒁀𒊑𒅁𒋢𒋢 𒇻 𒊭𒁀𒊑𒅁𒋢𒋢
jiri3 ur5-re gud ca-ba-ri-ib-su-su udu ca-ba-ri-ib-su-su

42.
𒅇 𒉡𒃻𒊏 𒈾𒀊𒁉𒂊
u3 nu-jar-ra na-ab-be2-e
42-43. You should not speak improperly; later it will lay a trap for you.

43.
𒂕𒁉𒂠 𒄑𒁖𒁶 𒅆𒈨𒅆𒌈𒇲𒂊
ejer-bi-ce3 jic-par3-gin7 ci-me-ci-ib2-la2-e

44.
𒌑 𒉡𒆥𒂷𒂠 𒇻𒍮 𒉺𒃶 𒉆𒈨
u2 nu-kij2-ja2-ce3 udu-zu sag2 nam-me
44-46. You should not scatter your sheep into unknown pastures. You should not hire someone's ox for an uncertain journey. A safe journey means a safe journey.

45.
𒍑 𒉡𒋧𒂵𒂠 𒄞 𒇽 𒈾𒂠𒂊
uc nu-sig10-ga-ce3 gud lu2 na-huj-e

46.
𒍑 𒋧𒂵 𒆜 𒋧𒂵𒀀𒀭
uc sig10-ga kaskal sig10-ga-am3

47.
𒆜 𒈪 𒈾𒀭𒁺 𒊮𒁉 𒊷 𒅆𒌨𒀀
kaskal ji6 na-an-du cag4-bi sag9 hul-a
47. You should not travel during the night: it can hide both good and evil.

48.
𒀲𒂔𒈾 𒈾𒀊𒉚𒉚 𒌓𒁕𒁉𒌍 𒉌𒂊
ance-edin-na na-ab-sa10-sa10 ud-da-bi-ec zal-e
48. You should not buy an onager: it lasts only until the end of the day.

49.
𒊩𒆳𒍮𒌫 𒄑𒁹𒁹𒁹 𒈾𒀭𒆕 𒍮𒌫 𒋗𒈬𒊑𒅔𒄷𒈾
geme2-zu-ur2 jic3 na-an-du3 zu-ur2 cu-mu-ri-in-sa4
49. You should not have sex with your slave girl: she will chew you up.

50.
𒀾 𒀉 𒍣 𒈾𒀊𒁄𒂊 𒋗𒍑 𒅎𒅆𒎏𒉎
ac2 a2 zig3 na-ab-bal-e cu-uc im-ci-ninni2
50. You should not curse strongly: it rebounds on you.

51.
𒀀 𒋗 𒉡𒁍𒄿 𒈾𒀭𒇯𒁺𒉈 𒀉 𒋝 𒋗𒈬𒂊𒊏𒅅
a cu nu-gid2-i na-an-ed3-de3 a2 sig cu-mu-e-ra-jal2
51-52. You should not draw up water which you cannot reach: it will make you weak.

52.
𒈤𒁉 𒃻𒁍𒄿 𒁀𒀭𒊒𒁉 𒃻𒂊 𒁀𒀭𒊒𒁉
mah-bi nij2-gid2-i ba-an-cub-be2 nij2-e ba-an-cub-be2

53.
𒄯 𒌇 𒈾𒀭𒁁𒂊 𒇽𒁉 𒊭𒁀𒂊𒉽
ur5 tuku na-an-bad-e lu2-bi ca-ba-e-kur2
53. You should not drive away a debtor: he will be hostile towards you.

54.
𒆗𒈾𒁕 𒂍 𒈾𒀭𒁕𒂷𒂷𒀭
sun7-na-da e2 na-an-da-ja2-ja2-an
54-57. You should not establish a home with an arrogant man: he will make your life like that of a slave girl. You will not be able to travel through any human dwelling without being shouted at: "There you go! There you go!"

55.
𒄄𒅔𒂠 𒁺𒉈 𒅆𒈨𒅆𒅁𒊒𒊒
gi4-in-ce3 du-de3 ci-me-ci-ib-cub-cub

56.
𒆠𒆪 𒇽𒅗 𒈾𒀊𒋫𒁄𒂊𒉈
ki-tuc lu2-ka na-ab-ta-bal-e-de3

57.
𒅆𒁺𒌦 𒅆𒁺𒌦 𒅆𒈨𒅆𒌈𒁉𒂊𒉈
ci-du-un ci-du-un ci-me-ci-ib2-be2-e-ne

58.
𒄀𒋝𒂵 𒄑𒊬𒅗 𒁕𒂵 𒉆𒉈𒂃𒂊𒂗
gi-sig-ga jickiri6-ka da-ga nam-bi2-du8-e-en
58-59. You should not undo the fence of the garden's reed enclosure; "Restore it! Restore it!" they will say to you.

59.
𒋢𒂵𒀊 𒋢𒂵𒀊 𒅆𒈨𒅆𒌈𒁉𒉈
sug6-ga-ab sug6-ga-ab ci-me-ci-ib2-be2-ne

60.
𒌨 𒉆𒈬𒌦𒅥𒂗 𒈌𒇽𒆕𒉈 𒉆𒃡𒃡𒊑𒂗
ur nam-mu-un-gu7-en du14 nam-ur3-ur3-re-en
60. You should not provide a stranger with food; you should not wipe out a quarrel.

61.
𒌉𒈬 𒉆𒍂 𒉆𒈬𒀝𒂗 𒇽 𒆠 𒉆𒍑𒂊𒂗
dumu-ju10 nam-silig nam-mu-ak-en lu2 ki nam-us2-e-en
61-62. My son, you should not use violence. You should not commit rape on someone's daughter; the courtyard will learn of it.

62.
𒌉 𒇽𒊏 𒄑𒁹𒁹𒁹 𒀉 𒍣 𒈾𒀭𒉈𒂗 𒆦𒂊 𒉈𒍮𒍮
dumu lu2-ra jic3 a2 zig3 na-an-ne-en kisal-e bi2-zu-zu

63.
𒀉 𒌇 𒈾𒀭𒁁𒂊𒂗 𒂦 𒂄𒄭 𒈾𒀭𒄢𒂊𒂗
a2 tuku na-an-bad-e-en bad3 cul-hi na-an-gul-e-en
63-64. You should not drive away a powerful man; you should not destroy the outer wall. You should not drive away a young man; you should not make him turn against the city.

64.
𒆗 𒈾𒀭𒁁𒂊𒂗 𒌷𒂠 𒈾𒀭𒄥𒊑𒂗
juruc na-an-bad-e-en iri-ce3 na-an-gur-re-en

65.
𒇽 𒅗 𒋝𒂵𒁲 𒅆 𒄑𒁄𒁶 𒅆𒉡𒉡
lu2 inim sig-ga-ke4 igi jicbal-gin7 ci-sir5-sir5
65-66. The eyes of the slanderer always move around as shiftily as a spindle. You should never remain in his presence; his intentions should not be allowed to have an effect on you.

66.
𒅆𒀀 𒉆𒁀𒂊𒁺𒁺𒁍𒉈𒂗 𒊮𒄀 𒈾𒈬𒌦𒉽𒉽
igi-a nam-ba-e-gub-gub-bu-de3-en cag4-ge na-mu-un-kur2-kur2

67.
𒇽 𒈜𒆷𒁶 𒂍 𒁽𒅗 𒅗 𒉆𒋻𒋻𒊑
lu2 lul-la-gin7 e2 kac-ka ka nam-tar-tar-re
67. You should not boast in beer halls like a deceitful man.

68.
𒆠 𒉆𒀴𒅗 𒌝𒈨𒋼 𒋗 𒈾𒀭𒄞𒄞𒉈
ki nam-nitah-ka um-me-tej3 cu na-an-gud-gud-de3
68-72. Having reached the field of manhood, you should not jump with your hand. The warrior is unique, he alone is the equal of many; Utu is unique, he alone is the equal of many. With your life you should always be on the side of the warrior; with your life you should always be on the side of Utu.

69.
𒌨𒊕 𒀸 𒈾𒉆 𒀸𒉌 𒇽 𒊹𒊏𒀀𒀭
ur-saj dili na-nam dili-ni lu2 car2-ra-am3

70.
𒌓 𒀸 𒈾𒉆 𒀸𒉌 𒇽 𒊹𒊏𒀀𒀭
dutu dili na-nam dili-ni lu2 car2-ra-am3

71.
𒌨𒊕𒁕 𒁺𒁍𒉈 𒍣𒍮 𒃶𒂗𒁕𒅅
ur-saj-da gub-bu-de3 zi-zu he2-en-da-jal2

72.
𒌓𒁕 𒁺𒁍𒉈 𒍣𒍮 𒃶𒂗𒁕𒅅
dutu-da gub-bu-de3 zi-zu he2-en-da-jal2

73.
𒂊 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾𒂠 𒈬𒌦𒉌𒅔𒊑
curuppagki-e dumu-ni-ra na-ce3 mu-un-ni-in-ri
73-75. Šuruppag gave these instructions to his son. Šuruppag, the son of Ubara-Tutu, gave these instructions to his son Zi-ud-sura.

74.
? 𒌉 𒂬𒌅𒌅𒁲
curuppagki dumu ubara-tu-tu-ke4

75.
𒍣𒌓𒋤𒁺 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾𒂠 𒈬𒌦𒉌𒅔𒊑
zi-ud-su3-ra2 dumu-ni-ra na-ce3 mu-un-ni-in-ri

76.
𒁹𒁹𒄰𒈠𒂠 𒂊 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾 𒈾𒈬𒌦𒊑𒊑
2-kam-ma-ce3 curuppagki-e dumu-ni-ra na na-mu-un-ri-ri
76-82. A second time, Šuruppag gave instructions to his son. Šuruppag, the son of Ubara-Tutu gave instructions to his son Zi-ud-sura: My son, let me give you instructions: you should pay attention! Zi-ud-sura, let me speak a word to you: you should pay attention! Do not neglect my instructions! Do not transgress the words I speak!

77.
? 𒌉 𒂬𒌅𒌅𒁲
curuppagki dumu ubara-tu-tu-ke4

78.
𒍣𒌓𒋤𒁺 𒌉𒉌𒊏 𒈾 𒈾𒈬𒌦𒊑𒊑
zi-ud-su3-ra2 dumu-ni-ra na na-mu-un-ri-ri

79.
𒌉𒈬 𒈾 𒂵𒊑 𒈾𒊑𒈬 𒃶𒆪
