274-276. This gift of words is something which soothes the mind; when it enters the palace, it soothes the mind. The gift of many words is like stars.

275.
𒈾𒊑 ? 𒌉 𒂬𒌅𒌅𒁲 𒈾 𒂵
na-ri curuppagki dumu ubara-tu-tu-ke4 na rig5-ga

276.
? 𒌉 𒂬𒌅𒌅𒁲 𒈾 𒂵
curuppagki dumu ubara-tu-tu-ke4 na rig5-ga

277.
𒎏 𒁾 𒃲𒃲𒆷 𒋗 𒌌𒀀
nin dub gal-gal-la cu du7-a
277. These are the instructions given by Šuruppag, the son of Ubara-Tutu.

278.
𒆠𒂖 𒀭𒊺𒉀𒄩 𒍠𒊩
ki-sikil dnisaba za3-mi2
278-280. Praise be to the lady who completed the great tablets, the maiden Nisaba, that Šuruppag, the son of Ubara-Tutu gave his instructions!

